      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so a lot of the debate seems to be about whether the growth it creates actually trickles down or if it just stays at the top. looking at the actual projections, is there a consensus on which school of thought is more likely to be right here? like, is the stimulus argument actually supported by the data, or is it more of a theoretical hope?",
